
// This Hyperlambda snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a specified location in the node graph. It retrieves nodes using [get-nodes] from the [.arguments] node, specifically targeting [limit] and [offset] nodes, and appends them to the path specified by the expression in [add]. This is useful for dynamically modifying the structure of a node graph based on input arguments.
add:x:@data.connect/*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
